model.name: archiAgent
model.documentation: Single Process diagram to demo LLM RAG-bot using the XML as knowledge base.

element.name: Consumer
element.documentation: Consumers (Business Actor) are individuals that either buy product from eCom sites selecting logyCorp as delivery option, or send parcels to other individuals via logyCorp.

element.name: Buy product delivered from eCom
element.documentation: When consumers select logyCorp as delivery provider in eCom webshop, they can select the service point they would want their parcel delivered to buy inputting their desired location. By buying the product from eCom with logyCorp as the selected delivery provider, the consumer instructs the eCom to use logyCorp for delivery. The eCom, not the consumer, is the customer of the parcel delivery from logyCorp. logyCorp deliveres the parcel to the consumer, not the eCom.

element.name: Load trolley cage into vehicle
element.documentation: Delivery driver scans the consolidated trolley cage of parcels with Transport Management System run in Mobile Scanner as loaded to vehicle.

element.name: Delivery Driver
element.documentation: Delivery Driver (Business Actor) is a logyCorp employee that drives a van (first or last mile delivery) or lorry (linehaul between logyCorp terminals). Delivery Drivers use Mobile Scanners running Transport Management System.

element.name: Unload trolley cage's parcels into sorter
element.documentation: When the delivery driver delivers a trolley cage to logyCorp terminal, logyCorp's warehouse staff unload the trolley cage's parcels into the terminal's sorter.

element.name: Warehouse Staff
element.documentation: Warehouse Staff (Business Actor) is a logyCorp employee that handles parcels in terminals. Warehouse Staff use Mobile Scanners running logyCorp ERP.

element.name: Load parcel from chute to route trolley cage
element.documentation: Warehouse Staff scan a parcel in the chute to find the trolley cage the parcel should be consolidated to. Warehouse Staff consolidate the parcel to a the designated trolley cage.

element.name: Load route trolley cage into vehicle and start delivery route
element.documentation: When delivery driver scans a trolley cage that returns consignment log with "Ready for delivery" for the delivery route of the delivery driver, the delivery driver loads the trolley cage into their vehicle using Mobile Scanner running Transport Management System. Delivery Driver loads trolleys storing consolidated parcels to vehicle for either linehaul to another logyCorp terminal or the last mile delivery to service point using Mobile Scanner running Transport Management System. Loading a consolidated unit to a vehicle records the "loaded to delivery" event to each parcel consolidated.

element.name: Shelve parcels into parcel locker
element.documentation: Delivery Driver loads parcels into parcel lockers using Transport Management System running on Mobile Scanner. Parcel locker door is opened via an admin code known by delivery drivers. The delivery driver scans each parcel shelved into a parcel locker with the Mobile Scanner running Transport Management System to log "At service point" status to the parcel. Transport Management System stores the status in logyCorp ERP consignment event log.

element.name: Fetch parcel from parcel locker stated using fetch code stated
element.documentation: When consumer receives a fetch notification and fetch code, the consumer knows to go fetch their parcel from the parcel locker using the given fetch code. When the consumer has fetched their parcel from the parcel locker a "Consignment fetched by consumer" event log is created, ending the delivery.

element.name: eCom platform
element.documentation: eCom platforms (external Application Components are usually Shopify or WooCommerce. Larger eCom businesses usually create their own eCom platform, often heavily dependent on their ERP system. Smaller eCom businesses start with just eCom platforms and do custom business processess (like making a transport order to logyCorp) manually.

element.name: logyCorp ERP
element.documentation: logyCorp ERP (Application Component) is a Java Monolith with a monolithic relational database. Using a three-layer architecture (Interface, Business Logic, Database), the ERP takes input from several systems (e.g., Transport Management System) and interfaces (Service Point API, Orders API, Notifications API), processess them with its business logic, and then stores in the database. This ensures that the master state is in the ERP's database, that the master business logic is the ERP's, and all systems recording consignment status events (e.g., Transport Management System, Orders API, Sorter, Mobile Scanner, Parcel Locker, etc.) will be centralised in the logyCorp ERP. These systems will also not have their own state of consignments, acting as I/O slaves of the ERP. logyCorp is hosted on AWS EC2-instances, load balanced with AWS ELB.

element.name: Service Point API
element.documentation: Service Point API (Application Interface) serves the eCom platform service points closest to the selected address. Service Point API is a REST API of logyCorp ERP. The eCom platform often utilises the by showing taking the address as input on the website from the consumer and showing the output service points to the consumer in the website. The eCom platform will bind the consumer's selected service point as the location where the transport order will be delivered to.

element.name: Orders API
element.documentation: Orders API (Application Interface) collect consignment orders from either eComs or logyCorp's internal services. Orders API is a REST API that serves the logyCorp ERP with an CRUD operation to an order. Creating an order will make a new consignment in the logyCorp ERP. Reading an order will return its status events. Updating an order will update the service point, consumer information, eCom information, delivery product, or deactivate the delivery. Deleting an order will delete the record of the order. Consignment events are recorded via point-to-point APIs beween logyCorp ERP and systems.

element.name: eCom's ERP
element.documentation: eCom's ERP (Application Component) is often a Warehouse Management System (WMS) that maintains the eCom's warehouse stock of products. Larger eCom's usually treat the eCom platform as an I/O slave to their WMS. Smaller eCom's usually use their eCom platform as WMS (e.g., to store warehouse stock).

element.name: Create transport order
element.documentation: Transport order is the eCom's record of a product needing to be delivered; a promise to create a consignment with logyCorp - logyCorp does not know of the eCom's transport orders before they become consigments via the Orders API. Transport order compiles consumer service point and contact details needed for creating a consignment.

element.name: Create consignment
element.documentation: Consignment is created by calling the Orders API. Orders API can be called by logyCorp's internal services or eComs. Creating a consignment sets consignment event to "created".

element.name: Create transport stop
element.documentation: Transport Management System creates a transport stop for the consignment triggered by the logyCorp ERP when a consignment is created.

element.name: Transport Management System
element.documentation: Transport Management System (Application Component) is a separate system from logyCorp ERP but all consignment data is stored solely in logyCorp ERP and fetched from there. Transport Management System creates routes, their stops, and stores delivery driver events logged from Mobile Scanners.

element.name: Notifications API
element.documentation: Notifications API (Application Interface) handles SMS Gateways, emails, and alerts in partner systems for logyCorp ERP. Notifications API is a REST API of logyCorp ERP. logyCorp ERP sends, for example, fetch code and notification SMS to consumer via Notifications API through using SMS Gateway service. Notifications API only sends, does not receive, messages.

element.name: Notify of fetchable parcel and fetch code
element.documentation: When consignment is at "At service point" status, logyCorp ERP sends a notification and fetch code to the consumer via Notifications API using SMS Gateway service. When the Notifications API confirms a successful message delivery to logyCorp ERP, logyCorp ERP creates a "Consignment fetch is notified" event log.

element.name: SMS Gateway service
element.documentation: SMS Gateway service (Application Component) is a SaaS-service for sending SMS messages, used by Notifications API. SMS Gateway only sends, does not receive, SMS messages.

element.name: Consignment created
element.documentation: "Created" status will be added as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Consignment fetched from warehouse
element.documentation: "Fetched from warehouse" status will be added retroactively once the parcel is scanned by sorter as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Consignment sorted
element.documentation: "Sorted" status will be added as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Consignment ready for delivery
element.documentation: "Ready for delivery" status will be added as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Consignment at service point
element.documentation: "At service point" status will be added as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Consignment fetch notified
element.documentation: "Fetch notified" status will be added as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Consignment fetched by consumer
element.documentation: "Fetched by consumer" status will be added as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Consignment measured
element.documentation: "Measured" status and measures will be added as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Consignment consolidated
element.documentation: "Consolidated" status and one-to-many foreign key with the consolidation id of the delivery trolley cage, stored in logyCorp ERP, will be added as the newest event in the consignment event log.

element.name: Sorter
element.documentation: Sorter (Equipment) is a terminal spanning conveyor belt with chutes. The input of the sorter stores a measure of parcel's dimensions (cubes) to logyCorp ERP and scans it to read the parcel's delivery postcode from logyCorp ERP. logyCorp ERP maintains a postcode-chute reference table for each sorter that sorters query. The sorter pushes the parcel to the correct chute on the conveyor belt. From the chute warehouse staff read parcels with mobile scanners running logyCorp ERP to find the trolley cage the parcel should be consolidated to.

element.name: Mobile Scanner
element.documentation: Mobile Scanners are MDM-managed Android phones running logyCorp ERP for warehouse staff and Transport Management System for delivery drivers.

element.name: Parcel Locker
element.documentation: Parcel Locker (Equipment) is a logyCorp service point type. logyCorp has parcel lockers and parcel stores as service points. Consignments are loaded to parcel lockers by delivery drivers and consignments are fetched from parcel lockers by consumers who have the consigments fetch code, generated and sent bt logyCorp ERP.

relationship.documentation: eCom platform calls Service Point API to show consumers the service points closest to them to select for delivery location

relationship.name: eCom's transport orders to logyCorp are stored in eCom's ERP
relationship.documentation: eCom's transport orders to logyCorp are stored in eCom's ERP

relationship.name: Create transport stop - Load trolley cage into vehicle
relationship.documentation: When a delivery driver drives a Transport Management System created route consisting of stops, one of those stops will be a the consignment

relationship.documentation: Warehouse Staff unload the delivery van's trolley cage's from eCom warehouses and unload their parcels into the sorter that scans and measures them

relationship.documentation: Every delivery route starts and terminates at the logyCorp terminal, so the fetched parcel will arrive at logyCorp terminal as terminus where it will be unloaded to a sorter

relationship.name: Warehouse Staff - Load parcel from chute to route trolley cage
relationship.documentation: Warehouse Staff scan a parcel in the chute to find the trolley cage the parcel should be consolidated to. Warehouse Staff consolidate the parcel to a the designated trolley cage.

relationship.documentation: The sorter stores the parcel's measure and sorting status to logyCorp ERP consignment event log

relationship.name: Sorter - Unload trolley cage's parcels into sorter

relationship.name: Mobile Scanner - Load route trolley cage into vehicle and start delivery route
relationship.documentation: Delivery Driver is using Mobile Scanner running Transport Management System to load trolley cage into vehicle. Once all trolley cages are loaded to vehicle, marks delivery route drive to have started on delivery driver starts driving delivery route on Mobile Scanner running Transport Management System

relationship.name: Delivery Driver - Load route trolley cage into vehicle and start delivery route
relationship.documentation: Delivery Driver uses Mobile Scanner running Transportation Management System to scan whether the route delivery trolley cage next to their loading bay is for their delivery route. If yes, Delivery Driver uses Mobile Scanner running Transportation Management System to load trolley cage into vehicle. Once all trolley cages are loaded to vehicle, marks delivery route drive to have started on delivery driver starts driving delivery route on Mobile Scanner running Transport Management System

relationship.documentation: Delivery Driver loads parcels into parcel lockers using Transport Management System running on Mobile Scanner

Load route trolley cage into vehicle and start delivery route - Shelve parcels into parcel locker
relationship.documentation: Once delivery route is at consignment's transport stop, Mobile Scanner running Transport Management System tells delivery driver which trolley cages is to be shelved into the stop's parcel locker

relationship.documentation: Because what consignments the eCom warehouse's trolley cage contains aren't known to logyCorp ERP, only once parcels are unloaded into a sorter that scans them can "Fetched from warehouse" status be retroactively logged to the consignment.

relationship.documentation: The sorter stores "Sorted" status in logyCorp ERP consignment event log

relationship.documentation: When a parcel is loaded to the route trolley cage, the consignment event status log "Ready for delivery" is added

relationship.documentation: When delivery driver logs in Mobile Scanner running Transport Management Systems that a parcel is shelved into a parcel locker, logyCorp ERP creates consignment event log status "At service point"

relationship.documentation: When a notification is sent, logyCorp ERP stores consignment event log as "fetch notified"

relationship.documentation: When the consumer has fetched their parcel from the parcel locker a "Consignment fetched by consumer" event log is created, ending the delivery.

relationship.documentation: The sorter stores "Measured" status and measures in logyCorp ERP consignment event log

relationship.documentation: When delivery driver scans a trolley cage that returns consignment log with "Ready for delivery" for the delivery route of the delivery driver, the delivery driver loads the trolley cage into their vehicle using Mobile Scanner running Transport Management System

view.name: Process - eCom order to parcel locker
view.documentation: This process diagram documents the logyCorp delivery process from consumer ordering a product delivered to a service point during their eCom purchase to the end of the consumer fetching the parcel from the parcel locker they selected. The consumer doesn't buy anything from logyCorp and isn't a direct customer of logyCorp. Instead, the eCom implicitly promises to procure a delivery from logyCorp for the consumer when the consumer selects logyCorp parcel locker delivery to a chosen location on their eCom order. logyCorp's delivery starts when the eCom creates a consignment with logyCorp's Orders API and the delivery ends when the consumer fetches the parcel from the parcel locker with a fetch code provided by logyCorp. The eCom pays logyCorp and the consumer paid the eCom. For customer service on the delivery, the consumer contacts logyCorp, for the product they contact the eCom.
